	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				My current strategy at lvl 6 is to cast grasping root on a target, then invoke lightining twice and one burst of flame.<BR>
By this time I am down on mana, so if the target is still moving I run up and attack, or let him come to me when root wears off.<BR>
I am North Ro, and this tactic works on pumas and orc raiders, but rattlesnakes tend to survive. I would not suggest trying it on them .<BR>
You will need mana to cast cure poson if you attack them.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
